    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-29T12:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-29T12:29:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/565</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-29T21:00:00+03:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 3, 11.40 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1823. Quiet to-day but Minister for Foreign Affairs says Bolsheviks circularizing
                    workmen and Bolshevik soldiers directing delegations be sent to conference and
                    protest against counter-revolutionary sentiment which seems prevailing there.
                    This may produce clash as workmen have [not] returned arms as commanded but
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs says Government confident can suppress outbreak and
                    such is also feeling of Minister of War who lunched at the Embassy to-day.
                    Cabled you <hi rend="italic">en chair</hi> placarded notice of protest meeting
                    to-morrow evening concerning America’s treatment of <persName>Alexander
                        Berkman</persName> of which I have notified Foreign Office. Notice unsigned
                    being evidently work of Bolsheviks. Cable immediately about Berkman’s crime and
                    prosecution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
